021, and one of Pasadena Magazine''s Top Lawyers for 2020 and 2021."},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-2","tag":"p","type":"text","children":[],"classNames":["text-size-medium"],"textContent":"Mr. Windsor currently shares his experience and expertise as an Adjunct Assistant Professor of Constitutional Law at a local law school in Los Angeles."},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-3","tag":"p","type":"text","children":[],"classNames":["text-size-medium"],"textContent":"Mr. Windsor spent his childhood on Martha''s Vineyard, an island off the coast of Cape Cod, Massachusetts. He graduated from Brown University with a B.A. in history, and then spent several years working abroad and traveling extensively. Mr. Windsor finally settled in California, where he attended law school at the University of California, Davis (Martin Luther King, Jr. School of Law). He now lives and works in Pasadena, California. His law office is located at 65 North Raymond Avenue, Suite 320, Pasadena, California 91103."},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-list-4","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-4","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-4-0","tag":"h4","type":"heading","children":[],"classNames":["heading-style-h4"],"textContent":"Bar Admissions"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-4-1","tag":"ul","type":"list","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-4-1-0","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"State Bar of California"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-4-1-1","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"California State Courts"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-4-1-2","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"U.S. District Court, Northern District of California"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-4-1-3","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"U.S. District Court, Central District of California"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-4-1-4","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"U.S. District Court, Southern District of California"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-4-1-5","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"U.S. Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit"}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_list"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"]},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-5","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-5-0","tag":"h4","type":"heading","children":[],"classNames":["heading-style-h4"],"textContent":"Education"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-5-1","tag":"ul","type":"list","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-5-1-0","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"J.D., University of California, Davis (Martin Luther King, Jr. School of Law)"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-1-0-1-0-item-5-1-1","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"B.A. in History, Brown University"}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_list"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_list"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_content"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_content"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_content"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"]},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-0","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-0-1","tag":"h3","type":"heading","children":[],"classNames":["heading-style-h3"],"textContent":"Katy Kimball Windsor"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-0-2","tag":"p","type":"text","children":[],"classNames":["text-size-small"],"textContent":"Partner"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-0-3","tag":"p","type":"text","children":[],"classNames":["text-size-small"],"textContent":"katy@windsorlaw.us (213) 663-9219"}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_content"]},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-0","tag":"p","type":"text","children":[],"classNames":["text-size-medium"],"textContent":"For nearly thirty years, Ms. Kimball Windsor has represented clients fighting criminal charges in federal court. Focused primarily on appellate practice, she has handled a wide variety of cases from white collar fraud to RICO, drug trafficking, and immigration crimes."},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-1","tag":"p","type":"text","children":[],"classNames":["text-size-medium"],"textContent":"She has represented numerous clients in the Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals, and is also an experienced trial lawyer who has litigated in the Central and Southern Districts of California. Before entering private practice, she served as a trial attorney at Federal Defenders of San Diego, Inc. from 1996 to 2002, and as a Supervising Attorney at the same office from 2002 to 2003."},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-2","tag":"p","type":"text","children":[],"classNames":["text-size-medium"],"textContent":"Ms. Kimball Windsor received her B.A. from Vassar College, and her J.D. from University of California, Davis, Martin Luther King, Jr. School of Law."},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-list-3","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-3","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-3-0","tag":"h4","type":"heading","children":[],"classNames":["heading-style-h4"],"textContent":"Education"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-3-1","tag":"ul","type":"list","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-3-1-0","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"J.D., University of California, Davis (Martin Luther King, Jr. School of Law)"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-3-1-1","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"B.A., Vassar College"}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_list"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"]},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-4","tag":"div","type":"box","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-4-0","tag":"h4","type":"heading","children":[],"classNames":["heading-style-h4"],"textContent":"Experience"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-4-1","tag":"ul","type":"list","children":[{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-4-1-0","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"Federal Defenders of San Diego, Inc., Trial Attorney (1996-2002)"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-4-1-1","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"Federal Defenders of San Diego, Inc., Supervising Attorney (2002-2003)"},{"id":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33-component-item-2-0-1-0-item-4-1-2","tag":"li","type":"listItem","children":[],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"],"textContent":"Private practice focused on federal criminal defense and appeals"}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_list"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_list"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_content"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_content"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_content"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_item"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_list"]}],"classNames":["attorney-profiles_component"]}],"classNames":["padding-section-medium"]}],"classNames":["container-large"]}],"classNames":["padding-global"]}],"classNames":["section_attorney-profiles"]},"reusableClasses":["padding-global","container-large","padding-section-medium","heading-style-h2","text-size-medium"],"sectionMetadata":{"pageId":"928cbe9e54d8c24f","repoId":"6214c13d4994a673","pageName":"About","sectionId":"0a9f7c5f8595ea33","sourceFile":"src/app/pages/about.tsx","sectionName":"Attorney Profiles"},"suggestedNewClasses":["section_attorney-profiles","attorney-profiles_component","attorney-profiles_list","attorney-profiles_item","attorney-profiles_content"]}', NULL, '2026-05-31T02:32:14.451Z', NULL);
